{"badges":["TM5","TM6"],"preparations":[{"title":"Goat's cheese flans and leeks","content":["Grease and flour 4 ramekins (approx. Ø 9 cm, height 5 cm) and set aside.","Place milk, goat's cheese, flour and salt in mixing bowl and mix <b>30 sec\/speed 5<b>.","Add egg yolks and mix <b>30 sec\/speed 4<b>. Transfer to a bowl and set aside. Clean and dry mixing bowl and lid thoroughly."," <strong>Insert butterfly whisk.<\/strong> Place egg whites in mixing bowl and whisk <b>2 min\/speed 3<b> or until stiff.","Add reserved mixed egg yolk mixture and whisk <b>30 sec\/speed 1.5<b>. <strong>Remove butterfly whisk.<\/strong> Transfer to prepared ramekins, arrange in Varoma dish and set aside. Clean mixing bowl.","Place water in mixing bowl. Insert simmering basket and add leeks and red peppers to it. Set Varoma containing ramekins in position and steam <b>18 min\/Varoma\/speed 1<b>. Set covered Varoma aside on a plate to keep flans warm. Remove simmering basket using spatula and set aside. Empty and clean mixing bowl."]},{"title":"Yoghurt sauce","content":["Place goat’s cheese, plain yoghurt, chives, salt and ground pepper in mixing bowl and mix <b>30 sec\/speed 4<b>. Adjust seasoning to taste.","Unmould flans by running a small thin knife around the inside edge of each ramekin, then place a plate on top of each ramekin and turn it over, carefully helping flan out of ramekin with knife if necessary. Arrange steamed leeks and red peppers around flans, drizzle with sauce and serve hot."]}],"ingredients":[{"title":"Goat's cheese flans and leeks","content":["butter, for greasing","40 g flour, plus extra for dusting","130 g milk","140 g fresh goat's cheese","½ tsp salt","2 eggs, separated","500 g water","300 g leeks, white part only, cut in pieces (5 mm)","50 g red peppers, diced (1 cm)"]},{"title":"Yoghurt sauce","content":["60 g fresh goat's cheese","125 g plain yoghurt","6 fresh chives, chopped","2 - 3 pinches salt","2 pinches ground pepper, adjust to taste"]}],"id":"r80469","imageLink":"https:\/\/2.bp.blogspot.com\/-4ef0PupwoW0\/XZMutn96j_I\/AAAAAAAAaI0\/O_LIBEp6w2oGntLtVaQ9CUpfKBeb1961QCLcBGAsYHQ\/s1600\/0_Pg_QjNnYj71nAlld.png","title":"Goat's cheese flans with yoghurt sauce and leeks","publishedAt":"2017-07-18T00:00:00Z","nutrition":{"protein":"13 g","fat":"14 g","uom":"per 1 portion","carbohydrates":"18 g","calories":"1089 kJ \/ 260 kcal"},"usefulItems":"ramekins (approx. Ø 9 cm, height 5 cm)","hintsAndTricks":["These delicate flans make a perfect starter or light lunch. The fresh herbed yoghurt sauce and the leeks steamed until meltingly soft offer a pleasant contrast to the hot cheese flans. Experiment with different types of soft cheeses to change the flavour of the dish.","The flans can also be served cold as a starter, with fresh green lettuce and diced tomatoes.","For a stronger flavour, replace goat’s cheese with <b>90 g blue<b> cheese (e.g. Gorgonzola) in the flan and <b>60 g blue<b> cheese in the yoghurt sauce."],"basicInfo":["easy","30m","45m","4 portions"]}